The water oxidation of these samples under AM 1.5G illumination in 0.5 M potassium phosphate buffer (pH 7.0) were obtained by a three-electrode configuration (Fig. 5
                        a and b). The results reveal that the onset potentials of Bi2Mo2O9, Bi2MoO6, and Bi2MoO6@Bi2Mo2O9 are 0.590, 0.330, and 0.320 V vs. RHE, respectively (Table 2
                        ), indicating that the onset potential of Bi2MoO6@Bi2Mo2O9 has a negatively shift compared with pristine Bi2Mo2O9 and Bi2MoO6 due to the reduced the energy barrier. Meanwhile, Bi2Mo2O9 and Bi2MoO6 generate a photocurrent density of 0.020 mA cm−2 and 0.045 mA cm−2 at 1.23 V vs. RHE, while the Bi2MoO6@Bi2Mo2O9 generates 0.160 mA cm−2 at the same potential, corresponding to an 8.0 and 3.6 times enhancement. The result indicates that Bi2MoO6@Bi2Mo2O9 hybrid structure is effectively improved the charge separation and surface charge oxidation kinetics efficiencies. Furthermore, this work could make comparison to the other references as shown in Table S3, indicating the PEC performance of Bi2MoO6@Bi2Mo2O9 is superior than most of other modified composite.
